<TITLE> 3 killed as Kolkata-bound bus crashes in Magura </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 14 (bdnew24.com)  At least three people were killed and 20 injured as a Kolkata-bound bus crashed in Magura on Saturday, said police. The Sohagh Paribahan, coming from Dhaka, lost control and veered into a roadside ditch, said Magura Sadar Police Station SI Khabir Hossain. The dead were identified as 55 year-old Kamala Ghosh, from Lalbagh in Dhaka, her son Prashanto Ghosh (35) and Abu Taher (50) of Fatikchhari in Chittagong. The injured were taken to Magura Sadar hospital, he said. Of them three were Indian citizens. The passengers blamed the driver's "grogginess" for the accident. bdn
